</div>
				
				<div>
					
					
				</div>
				<div>   </div>
			</div>					
		
	</td>
	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div><br /> Yes, I read it. The meat of his argument is that the government has no right to spend money beyond that which is described by the Constitution, and that to do is to frivolously spend others' money. <br />
<br />
The theory fails because Bunce (and Crockett, who obviously is making the same argument) doesn't understand what the Constitution allows; they don't understand that the main job of an elected official is to disburse The People's money as situations warrant. <br /></div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
